Done — I updated `sdks/browser4-cli/tests/e2e.rs` so each browser-backed E2E scenario now gets a freshly restarted `Browser4` backend on a new free port.

Why this fixed it: the old harness kept reusing one backend URL/process across scenarios, so state/process leakage could carry over.
The new `E2ETestResources::restart_browser4()` resets the server before every scenario and rewires `ctx.browser4_base_url` to that fresh instance.

I validated it with:

`cd sdks/browser4-cli && cargo fmt && cargo test --test e2e -- --nocapture`

Result: all 5 E2E tests passed.


